hic and lifestyle.  While this decision regarding categorisation may well exercise some degree of influence on the packaging and, possibly, certain of the intrinsic features of the product, there is no clearly evident relationship between these factors and
 the category in which the brand is placed.  The building of a brand and its placement in one or other of the categories listed above appear to be mostly concerned with the construction, through various mechanisms of promotion, of a desired image and, ther
efore, association with a class of consumers.}
