\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li644\ri0\lin644\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 112.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch As we have already intimated, we believe that distribution and promotion must be carefully distinguished when measuring the extent of foreclosure.  The extent of foreclosed distribution can be measured relatively easily.  If BATSA enters into an exclusive 
distribution agreement with a chain of grocery stores \'96 that is, an agreement that provides that only BATSA products will be available in the chain\'92s cigarette category - the extent of foreclosure will simply be measured by the chain\'92s share of cigarette s
ales.  Promotion, on the other hand, embodies qualitative dimensions that cannot be so easily measured.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 113.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch That having been said it is, at this juncture, appropriate that we restate our view that there is, when assessing the extent of foreclosure of promotional opportunities, a definite interface with the fact of universal distribution. It is, through long esta
blished practice, well appreciated and understood that all brands and SKUs of any significance, and a great many without any significance, are available at all outlets from which cigarettes are sold.  This is certainly true of organised retail and of much 
of independent convenience.  It is, for space reasons, not true of the vending machines at the HORECA venues but these will be dealt with separately.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f2\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 114.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0 Moreover because cigarettes are not sold from the open, self service shelves but have rather to be requested from an attendant at a dedicated kiosk or at the till, the purchaser does not have to browse the shelf in order to find her brand. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 115.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch In short, a cigarette purchaser knows full well that her brand will be available at the POS, and, because of the loyalty element that characterises cigarette purchases, she knows full well what brand she will be purchasing before she even approaches the PO
S, and, even if she does not spot her brand on the CDU, she will merely have to ask the attendant to supply it.  All of this serves to reduce significantly the influence of the retail shelf or POS over cigarette brand purchasing, certainly where the establ
ished smoker is concerned.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{ Mr. Baker, JTI\'92s economist, conceded that in assessing the impact of the POS on choice one would make, in the words of BATSA;s counsel, \'91}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i huge allowances for the fact that well I\'92m dealing with a product that has an enormous amount of brand loyalty and }{\ul\ulc0\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i I\'92m
 dealing with a product that  people asked for whether they see it or not.\'92 }}}}
{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\rtlch\af2 }{\rtlch\af2   If the purchaser was not certain of the availability of her chosen brand, then indeed a limited amount of shelf browsing may take place before the selection of the brand takes place and relative space and positioning may then a
ssume more importance over brand selection.  However, that the consumer knows full well that distribution is universal is a key factor that reduces the importance of the POS as a site of promotion, and this is further reduced by the intermediation of an at
tendant and the fact of brand loyalty which, for most smokers, predetermines the choice of brand.  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 116.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch As noted above, this is unlikely to apply with the same strength to a first time smoker.  That is, someone who has little or no pre-conceived idea of the brand that she wants to purchase is more likely to be influenced by space and positioning on the shelv
es than would the experienced smoker.  However, given the overriding importance that the applicants have attached to peer pressure and social signals in the selection of a cigarette brand, it is likely, on the applicants\'92 own argument, that a significant p
ortion of even first time or inexperienced smokers will approach a retailer\'92s cigarette kiosk with a reasonably clear idea of the brand that she wishes to purchase.  As already noted we give little credence to the contention of Mr. Scammel Katz, JTI\'92s mark
eting expert, that cigarette purchasers would be too \'91embarrassed\'92 to ask for a brand that they could not immediately see on the CDU.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 117.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch In brief then our approach is that while distribution foreclosure and promotional foreclosure are to be measured using distinctive criteria \'96 the former purely quantitative, the latter with a strong qualitative dimension \'96 there is, certainly as far as the
 established smoker is concerned, a strong inverse relationship between the known fact of universal distribution (that is, the complete absence of distributional foreclosure) and the importance of the POS as a site of promotion.  }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 118.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch The huge edifice of this case then comes to rest on an extremely narrow platform.  The conduct alleged relates to plannogramming (space and position in the CDUs and vending machines), exclusivity over secondary displays and sundry acts of sabotage (removal
 by BATSA of rivals\'92 secondary display material).  Also at issue are exclusive opportunities allegedly purchased by BATSA for hosting promotional events at HORECA venues. While JTI continues to hold both space and positioning important to its case, the Com
mission\'92s counsel tells us that his client views position as the critical element.  Both the Commission and JTI argue vehemently that independent convenience is an ineffective site for promotional opportunities and so, they insist, are non-metropolitan are
as. It is agreed that promotion is directed overwhelmingly at young adult smokers or first time smokers but it appears that the \'91main market\'92, the cigarette industry\'92s particular euphemism for black smokers, is not considered fertile ground for the promoti
on of popular and, certainly, premium brands.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\loch\fs20 More specifically,}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\cf3\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\loch\fs20  }{\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\loch\fs20 JTI claims that it does not consider the low income market a credible market at which to direct the promotion of premium and popular brands.  BATSA disagrees.}{\cf3\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\loch\fs20  }{\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\loch\fs20 Note the following exchange at T5980-1 between JTI\'92s counsel and Mr. Wittenbe
rg, a BATSA executive:}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\rtlch \ltrch\loch \'93}}{{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0 ADV UNTERHALTER: And I\'92m assuming that particularly when we think about premium brands and so on, they are often directed towards the better off people that you marked out as being around R10\~000 a month. They are the class who are less price resistant.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\fs20\i\loch\fs20\i MR WITTENBERG: No, no, no, no, it\'92s actually interestingly in South Africa the other way around. The poorest part of the market, which are the black consumers, they actually have the highest premium brand incidence and high levels of your loyalty. They wou
ld rather smoke less. They smoke, a consumer, only 6,7,8 cigarettes per day but they want Peter Stuyvesant, versus in the white market there is the highest incidence of value-for-money brands. And as you\'92ve seen in the switching analysis that you\'92ve taken 
me to earlier, in the white consumer segment there is the highest down-trading\'94.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\cf3\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs20\lang1033\loch\f2\fs20\lang1033 }}
{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\rtlch\af2 }{\rtlch\af2  And it is agreed that promotional activity is directed as supporting premium and popular brands and not at VFM brands. }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 119.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch The core of the Commission and JTI\'92s case is then narrowed to the influence of position in the CDUs at organised retail and in vending machines, with JTI still arguing that allocation of space at these points of sale is important, to sundry acts of sabotag
e (although this has generated more atmosphere than evidence), and to promotional events at selected HORECA venues. Moreover the promotional activity with which the applicants are concerned is overwhelmingly that directed at influencing young, predominantl
y white, adult smokers who reside and entertain themselves in the upmarket parts of the metropolitan areas, a small sub-set of the smoking population, in their choice of premium and popular brand segments of the cigarette market.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 120.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch This all adds up to a very slender basis upon which to claim significant foreclosure, not to mention far-reaching remedies. There is clearly some substance in the observation of BATSA\'92s counsel that its opponents have narrowed the basis of their concern pr
ecisely in order to ensure that the scale of foreclosure increases relative to the ever diminishing universe identified as viable for promotion.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{ BATSA characterizes the applicants\'92 approach as }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i \'91a wholly transparent attempt, first to construct a \'91promotions market\'92, and then progressively to discard various parts of that \'91market\'92 until a \'91market\'92 was  yielded that was sufficiently small and focused
 around BATSA\'92s activities to create the impression of foreclosure.}{\'92 BATSA HOA para 8.36}}}}
{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\rtlch\af2 }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 121.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch Indeed, the approach of the applicants serves mainly to draw attention to the really fearsome gorilla in the room and that is the regulations that have prohibited above-the-line advertising and sponsorship. In other words if this is all that is left of the
 once ubiquitous juggernaut of cigarette brand promotion, then it speaks volumes about what was removed by the regulations.  And so even if the applicants had been able to prove all of the elements of their case \'96 and we do not believe this to be so - it w
ould be difficult to conclude that the significant element of foreclosure, and therefore the cause of any harm, inferred or otherwise, comes from the conduct of BATSA rather than from the decisions of the legislature whose manifest intent was to limit, ind
eed to eliminate, the promotion of cigarette sales.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 122.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch The promotional theory that is advanced places peer and social pressure at the centre of a smoker\'92s brand choice. It is accepted that young adult smokers are the principal target of promotional activity. These are either first time smokers or smokers relat
ively uncommitted to \'91their\'92 brand and therefore susceptible to switch brands as a result of promotional activities.  The sites at which young adults congregate are HORECA venues. The extent and character of social pressure generated by HORECA venues varie
s from venue to venue.  Only a select number of HORECA venues have, we are told, the }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i cachet}{\rtlch which generates social pressure to conform to the brands with which the venue has associated itself and the choices of the venue\'92s clientele.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi0\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 123.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s4\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li284\ri0\lin284\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch Having been influenced by the association of a desirable HORECA venue and its clientele with a particular brand, the young smokers or would-be smokers will endeavour to purchase their chosen brands at one or other of the retail outlets.  It is agreed that 
very few of the actual purchases take place at the vending machines in the HORECA venues (of course only a very small proportion of the target demographic of the cigarette manufacturer\'92s promotional efforts actually attend these venues and those who do wou
ld tend to bring their cigarettes with them).}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0 Of course the association is meant to appeal far beyond those who actually attend these salubrious venues.  Just as the vast majority of Stuyvesant smokers of yore will never have gone to St. Moritz, or the vast mast majority of Camel smokers will never h
ave crashed fearlessly through the Amazon, it is the association with those people and those places that is thought to appeal, possibly most especially to those who will never visit there.  So too with glamorous and expensive HORECA venues.}}}
