hisors is not clear and this will surely significantly influence the extent of franchisee compliance.  Our previous experience with franchise arrangements would suggest that the pass through of supplier incentives from franchisor to franchisee is an arena 
of considerable contestation between the parties to such an arrangement.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\ql{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  { }}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i Simelane & Others NO v Seven Eleven Corporation SA (Pty) Ltd & Another}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{  [2001-2002] CPLR 13 (SCA)}}}}
