re in the urban areas, which are the only localities that JTI identified as significant from a promotional perspective.}{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0{ BATSA HOA para 150.1. We note that Mr. Baker, the JTI economist, dismissed these as \'91relatively marginal activities around a core of BATSA controlled outlets\'92.  This is not a credible assessment of either JTI\'92s achievements in this channel (particularly w
