\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-709\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 239.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch Thirdly, while BATSA has undoubtedly spent considerable sums on POS promotion, it has, as we shall show, also spent considerable sums on direct marketing, of which HORECA is a particular case. Our interpretation of the evidence is that, absent the ability 
to exercise social and peer group pressure through above the line advertising and sponsorship, direct marketing, including, but not limited to, the hosting of events at HORECA venues, is likely to be the most effective form of promotion in the cigarette ca
tegory.  With the important exception of HORECA it is not alleged, and nor could it be, that BATSA has somehow contrived to foreclose direct marketing opportunities. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-709\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 240.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch Fourthly, given BATSA\'92s market share it does retain a clear incentive to promote the category. As has been frequently pointed out BATSA\'92s huge market share presupposes that its share of growth in the category is similarly significant.  Indeed it is this fe
ature of the market that makes BATSA the obvious category manager \'96 it cannot afford not to promote the category. Accordingly it should be acknowledged that a significant part of its trade marketing spend is rationally directed at promotional activity from
 which the entire category, including BATSA\'92s rivals, benefits. For example, the provision of free merchandising furniture and the incentive payments designed to keep the CDU free of non-tobacco products certainly have a significant category promotion aspe
ct.   The conduct which is in question \'96 the limited exclusive with respect to space, position and secondary display - represents BATSA\'92s attempts to secure a private advantage from a POS into which it has invested without the ability to appropriate a priv
ate return, at least without the ability to ensure that part of the return is not appropriated by its rivals.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-709\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 241.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0\rtlch Accordingly, the suggestion that BATSA\'92s trade investment spend infers its calculus of the importance of the POS as a site of brand promotion must, if it is to be at all useful, be based on that part of its trade investment spend that is directed at promot
ing its own brands, and should not include that part of its trade investment spend that is directed at supporting the category.  It is, of course, extremely difficult to separate these.   However there is, in our view, no doubt that a very significant part
 of the BATSA\'92s trade investment spend promotes the category, from which BATSA\'92s rival\'92s benefit, at least to the extent of their share of the category.}
