\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s16\sl480\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-709\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 245.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch It appears that while there are still many instances where cigarettes are sold from behind the bar or at the till, vending machines are increasingly the preferred mechanism for selling cigarettes in upmarket and midmarket HORECA venues, that is those venue
s which, as we shall see, are deemed appropriate for promotional purposes. Cigarette vending machines are not owned by HORECA outlets but by one of a number of vending machine operators who own, operate, install and maintain vending machines.   The prefere
nce of HORECA venue owners for vending machines over other forms of distribution relates to the threat of pilferage and the desire to avoid having to trade in a product that is not core to their businesses, particularly as it represents a negligible portio
n of the revenues of any single venue. Indeed, as already indicated, sales of cigarettes in HORECA venues represent 15% of total cigarette sales of which vending machines account for just 0.7%.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\ql{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0 Commission File D p158-185. Shebeens accounted for over 14% of the cigarette sales in this channel.}}}
{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\rtlch\af2 }{\rtlch\af2  }}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\li720\ri0\lin720\rin0\fi-709\rtlch\af2\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\f2\fs22\lang7177\f0\fs22\f4\fs20\lang1025\sl276\slmult1\qj 246.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\sl276\slmult1\qj{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls2\li295\ri0\lin295\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs22\lang7177\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\rtlch The South African cigarette vending market is highly concentrated with five VMOs accounting for over 93% of cigarette sales by volume and 83% of cigarette vending machines.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs22\lang7177\i0\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\ql{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0 BATSA Vending Account Plan 2002, Commission File D p132-134}}}
{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up9\rtlch\af11\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f0\fs24\lang1033\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\rtlch\af2 }{\rtlch\af2  Mr Ari Zelezniak of Vendomatic and \'93Magic Vending\'94, the largest of the VMOs, gave 
evidence before the Tribunal. He testified that the VMOs run their businesses as independent operators and not as agents of cigarette manufacturers and wholesalers, that is, they are retailers in their own right. As with any retailer they derive their prof
its from the sale of cigarettes from the margins that they charge over the wholesale purchase price. They charge higher prices than those charged in any of the other channels. The VMOs contract with the venue owners to put their machines in the premises of
 the venue owners and pay them a commission on each packet of cigarettes sold.}{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s13\sl240\slmult1\ql{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af4\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af0\langfe255\hich\f2\fs20\lang7177\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177{\*\cs68\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f2\fs20\lang7177\i0\b0 T1300}}}
