siderably more persuasive theoretical standpoint than that which relies on adherence to the principles of category management \'96 which is predicated on the neutralisation of competition for shelf space \'96 and the vague consumer benefits that are postulated t
o result from this.  Ultimately the impact on competition of any form of exclusive arrangement must be measured by the extent of foreclosure that results from the agreement.  As noted, we have exhaustively examined the evidence and we find that there is no
